\begin_layout Itemize
Under an applied field 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{E}_{0}$
\end_inset

, induced dipoles in the solid create an opposing field 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{E}_{1}$
\end_inset

.
 The field inside the material is 
\begin_inset Formula $\boxed{\mathcal{E}=\mathcal{E}_{0}+\mathcal{E}_{1}}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

